    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Judy Solanki</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2014/10/even-on-a-good-day/#comment-42233"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-10-25T16:40:03-04:00">Saturday, October 25, 2014 at 4:40 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>This is a discussion I have had with my husband time and time again. He looks around at the large collection of cookbooks I have, mentions large and delicious dinner party menus I have made and mumbles about the dinner I have just prepared. He wonders if I&#39;ve been busy that day and that&#39;s why there&#39;s not a 5 course meal on the table. I love to cook, but often don&#39;t love the tedium of it. </p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-42233' data-commentid="42233" data-postid="68" data-belowelement="comment-42233" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Judy Solanki" aria-label='Reply to Judy Solanki'>Reply</a>    </div>
