      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/09398802177166008567" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Sara Thompson</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2014/10/even-on-a-good-day/#comment-42271"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-10-27T15:48:38-04:00">Monday, October 27, 2014 at 3:48 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;m a food writer and an amazing cook but do you know how many times my family gets spaghetti for dinner (with various sauces and toppings)?  Just because it&#39;s not &#8220;special&#8221; doesn&#39;t mean you aren&#39;t cooking or loving the act.  Too many fancy dishes and they become everyday.  It&#39;s the everyday foods we remember &#8211; the ones we turn to for comfort.  The ones we pass onto our children.  It&#39;s the ones that remind us where home is.</p>
    </div>

